overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking validation against a detailed specification and
  identification of any missing functionalities. The agent conducted a thorough
  analysis of the existing codebase, comparing it with the provided requirements
  for an interactive questionnaire, report generation, data capture, and
  specific sleep disorder detection. This review resulted in a prioritized list
  of missing features. Following this, the agent began implementing the
  high-priority items. It successfully integrated a 1-10 severity scale for
  tiredness, complete with safety warnings for high scores, across the
  questionnaire UI, data models, and both web and PDF reports. Additionally, the
  agent implemented detection logic for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea
  (COMISA), ensuring appropriate messaging and recommendations are displayed in
  the generated reports.
